  "contentHtml": "<figure><a href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/%24s_!7mlL!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84c072f1-91f4-4621-9f80-5d30fff485be_5046x3567.jpeg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n<img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/%24s_!7mlL!,w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84c072f1-91f4-4621-9f80-5d30fff485be_5046x3567.jpeg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"848\" data-size=\"large\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n\n\n</a></figure>\n<p>I’m writing this from a McDonald’s in Northern Indiana, blasting top forty (oh-ee, Makeba, Makeba ma qué bella, Can I get a “Ooh-ee”? Makeba, Makes my body dance for you) as it snows another four inches outside. It wasn’t supposed to snow today, but four inches of snow when it wasn’t supposed to snow has been the normal for the last week.</p>\n<p>\n          <a href=\"https://walkingtheworld.substack.com/p/not-walking-chicago\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n              Read more\n          </a>\n      </p>",
